summary: This is a bank account statement from the Municipal Credit Union (MCU) for February 2019, showing transactions including deposits from the Department of Justice and the Department of Agriculture, and numerous retail purchases in the New York area. The document appears to be part of financial records related to the Epstein case, potentially for an individual receiving government payments.

keyFacts: The account holder received two federal salary deposits from the Department of Agriculture (AGRI TREAS 310) totaling approximately $4,681.17 in February 2019.
The account holder received a $600.00 miscellaneous payment from the Department of Justice (DOJ TREAS 310) on February 4, 2019.

Transaction patterns show frequent retail purchases at stores in Brooklyn, Manhasset, Garden City, and other New York locations, including jewelry stores (Helzberg Diamonds, Tiffany & Co.), clothing stores, and restaurants.
The account statement shows a net decrease in the checking balance over the month, with total withdrawals of $6,377.65 and total deposits of $5,281.17.

The document is a standard bank statement with no direct mention of Jeffrey Epstein, his associates, or victims, suggesting it may be a financial record of a peripheral figure or unrelated account included in the document set.
